\begin_layout Standard
Concretely,
 each pass through Algorithm 1 maps to the following steps.
 The archive is trimmed at the start of the loop (line 2).
 Branch selection happens in lines 3–7:
 a forced ARQ warm-up while the bootstrap counter 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{bs}>0$
\end_inset

 (lines 3–4),
 after which the Thompson bandit samples a branch from 
\begin_inset Formula $\{(a_{k},b_{k})\}$
\end_inset

 (lines 5–6).
 The chosen branch is then executed in lines 8–14:
 the IDE update (Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-ide"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

) if 
\begin_inset Formula $k=\mathrm{IDE}$
\end_inset

 (line 9),
 or,
 on the ARQ side,
 an eigen-basis refresh if stale (Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-eigen"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 line 11),
 the ARQ trial generation and RTR selection (Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-arq"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 line 12),
 and the Lévy-flight quarantine correction (Algorithm (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-quarantine"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 line 13).
 The bandit posterior for the executed branch is updated immediately afterward (line 15).
 Two independent stagnation signals are then maintained:
 the ordinary counter 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

,
 reset on any improvement and incremented otherwise (lines 16–20),
 and the meaningful-gain counter 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{p}$
\end_inset

\SpecialChar allowbreak
 (line 21),
 which gates the elite polish (Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-polish"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

) once 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{p}\geq\tau_{p}$
\end_inset

\SpecialChar allowbreak
 (line 22).
 The remaining stabilization mechanisms fire in sequence and are each individually gated:
 the OBL basin escape (Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-obl"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

) once 
\begin_inset Formula $s\geq\tau_{s}$
\end_inset

\SpecialChar allowbreak
 and the population spread has collapsed (line 23),
 and the hard-stagnation rejuvenation check (Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-rejuv"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

),
 which evaluates its own survival/hard-stagnation conditions internally (line 24).
 The population is then shrunk toward its current NLPSR target size if needed (Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:sparq-nlpsr"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 line 25),
 the bandit posteriors are decayed toward their uninformative prior (line 26),
 and the archive is trimmed a second time before the stopping state is updated and the current incumbent reported (lines 27–28).
\end_layout

