\begin_layout Subsection
Comparative Results on Standard-Dimensionality Benchmark Problems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This subsection presents the outcome of the comparative evaluation on the standard-dimensionality portion of the benchmark suite.
 SPARQ is compared against nine state-of-the-art optimizers:
 ARQ2 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "ARQ2"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 EA4Eig 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "EI4Eig"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 jSO 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "JSO"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 LM-CMA-ES 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "LMCMAES"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 mLSHADE-RL 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "mLSHADE-RL"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 NL-SHADE-LBC 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "NL-SHADE-LBC"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 SFCDE 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "SFCDE"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 TridentDE 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "TridentDE"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 and UDE3 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "UDE3"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 The comparison covers forty-five benchmark problems.
 These include classical synthetic test functions alongside real-world engineering formulations,
 such as antenna array design,
 hydrothermal scheduling,
 economic load dispatch,
 and several chemical-engineering problems.
 Problem dimensionality in this subsection ranges from as few as five variables to several hundred.
 For each problem,
 every method was executed independently over a fixed number of repeated runs under an identical evaluation budget.
 Three complementary tables report the results.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:comparison1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 presents detailed statistics for each method and problem,
 namely the best value found,
 the mean value,
 the success rate,
 the standard deviation,
 and the execution time.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:bestRankin1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports the ranking of all ten methods on each problem according to the best value achieved.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:meanRanking1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports the corresponding ranking according to the mean value,
 offering a stricter measure of reliability across repeated runs.
 Together,
 these three tables allow the performance of SPARQ to be assessed both in absolute terms and relative to its competitors,
 and both in terms of peak performance and average-case consistency.
\end_layout

