\begin_layout Standard
Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:bestRankin1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports the ranking of each method according to its best-value result.
 It covers the same ten methods and forty-five problems.
 SPARQ attains rank 1,
 whether shared or exclusive,
 on 25 of the 45 problems.
 This corresponds to 55.6%,
 the highest share among all ten methods.
 If only cases where SPARQ is the sole method at rank 1 are counted,
 with no ties,
 this figure falls to 4 of 45,
 or 8.9%.
 By comparison,
 jSO achieves 5 of 45 exclusive first places,
 and ARQ2 achieves 3 of 45.
 This indicates that a substantial part of SPARQ's rank-1 share arises from problems where several methods jointly reach the global optimum,
 rather than from unique dominance.
 The mean rank across all forty-five problems is 2.64 for SPARQ.
 This is the lowest,
 and therefore best,
 mean rank of the ten methods.
 It sits ahead of jSO at 2.80 and ARQ2 at 2.91.
 At the other extreme,
 LM-CMA-ES and NL-SHADE-RSP average 6.38 and 6.29 respectively.
 They register the worst rank,
 10th,
 on 20 problems (44.4%) and 11 problems (24.4%) respectively.
