Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:bestRankin2"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports the best-value ranking of the same six large-scale methods across the thirty-four problem-dimension combinations.
 SPARQ achieves rank 1,
 shared or exclusive,
 in 31 of 34 cases,
 or 91.2%.
 This is the highest share among all six methods.
 Its exclusive,
 untied first-place count is 7 of 34,
 or 20.6%.
 This is higher than any competitor.
 MMES attains 2 of 34 exclusively,
 and all others attain 0.
 SPARQ's mean rank across the thirty-four cases is 1.15,
 the best of the six methods.
 MMES follows at 1.41 and RMES at 1.47.
 There are two exceptions to SPARQ's first-place standing.
 On lunacekbirastrigin (d=10,000) it ranks 2nd.
 On vincent,
 at both dimensions,
 it ranks 3rd.
 VkD-CMA-ES,
 by contrast,
 shares rank 1 with the other five methods on every problem at d=1000.
 It drops to rank 6,
 the worst position,
 on every single problem at d=10,000.
 Overall it registers the worst rank in 20 of 34 cases,
 or 58.8%.
 This pattern indicates a pronounced scalability limitation at the highest dimensionality tested.
\end_layout

